				\begin{document}$$C * 1000$$\end{document} is the total number of drivers in the system) based on CAV advantage, Effect of changing to CAV, Effect of remaining HDV and Perceived effect of remaining HDV, see Fig. 5. For small congestion levels the effect or remaining HDV is negative and this negativity deepens with increasing CAV share. Contrariwise, the effect of changing to CAV is positive. Very high congestion levels result in the agents being indifferent to whether they change into a CAV or remain HDV. For intermediate congestion, CAV advantage is negative and Effect of remaining HDV positive, the more so the larger the CAV share.

